
Overview of noun commitment

The noun commitment has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (2) committedness, commitment -- (the trait of sincere and steadfast fixity of purpose; "a man of energy and commitment")
2. (2) commitment, allegiance, loyalty, dedication -- (the act of binding yourself (intellectually or emotionally) to a course of action; "his long commitment to public service"; "they felt no loyalty to a losing team")
3. (1) commitment -- (an engagement by contract involving financial obligation; "his business commitments took him to London")
4. commitment, dedication -- (a message that makes a pledge)
5. commitment, committal, consignment -- (the official act of consigning a person to confinement (as in a prison or mental hospital))
